<i>noun</i>: 희롱 [히롱], 조소 [조소], 조롱 [조롱], 웃음거리 [우슴꺼리], 우롱 [우롱], 비웃음 [비ː우슴] <i>verb</i>: 희롱하다 [히롱하다], 조소하다 [조소하다], 조롱하다 [조롱하다], 우롱하다 [우롱하다], 비웃다 [비ː욷따], 갉다 [각따] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>희롱 [히롱]</dt><br>
<dd>1. ridicule; taunt</dd><br>
<dd>특별한 이유나 실속이 없이 놀림.</dd><br>
<dd>To make fun of someone for no reason or without any real substance.</dd><br>
<dd>2. flirting; dallying; deceiving</dd><br>
<dd>사람을 제멋대로 가지고 놂.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of manipulating someone to use him/her at will.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>조소 [조소]</dt><br>
<dd>ridicule; derision</dd><br>
<dd>상대를 얕보거나 놀리거나 흉을 보듯이 웃는 일. 또는 그런 웃음.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of laughing in such a way that one looks like he/she is belittling, making fun of or speaking ill of the other person, or such laugh.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>조롱 [조롱]</dt><br>
<dd>ridicule</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 대상을 얕잡아 보고 비웃거나 놀림.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of mocking or taunting someone because one thinks nothing of him/her.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>웃음거리 [우슴꺼리]</dt><br>
<dd>1. laughing stock; scorn; derision; ridicule</dd><br>
<dd>남에게 비웃음을 당할 만한 일.</dd><br>
<dd>The behavior that deserves to be laughed at by others.</dd><br>
<dd>2. laughing stock; fool</dd><br>
<dd>남에게 비웃음을 당할 만한 사람.</dd><br>
<dd>A person who deserves to be laughed at by others.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>우롱 [우롱]</dt><br>
<dd>mockery; derision; ridicule</dd><br>
<dd>남을 어리석고 하찮게 여겨 함부로 대하거나 놀림.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of considering someone foolish and insignificant, and thus treating him/her disrespectfully or making fun of him/her.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>비웃음 [비ː우슴]</dt><br>
<dd>ridicule; sneer; scornful laughter</dd><br>
<dd>상대를 얕보거나 놀리거나 흉을 보듯이 웃는 일. 또는 그런 웃음.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of laughing disdainfully, mockingly, and scornfully; or such laughter</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>verb</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>희롱하다 [히롱하다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. ridicule; taunt</dd><br>
<dd>특별한 이유나 실속이 없이 놀리다.</dd><br>
<dd>To make fun of someone for no reason or without any real substance.</dd><br>
<dd>2. flirt; dally; deceive</dd><br>
<dd>사람을 제멋대로 가지고 놀다.</dd><br>
<dd>To manipulate someone to use him/her at will.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>조소하다 [조소하다]</dt><br>
<dd>ridicule; deride</dd><br>
<dd>상대를 얕보거나 놀리거나 흉을 보듯이 웃다.</dd><br>
<dd>To laugh in such a way that one looks like one is belittling, making fun of or speaking ill of the other person.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>조롱하다 [조롱하다]</dt><br>
<dd>ridicule</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 대상을 얕잡아 보고 비웃거나 놀리다.</dd><br>
<dd>To mock or taunt someone because one thinks nothing of him/her.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>우롱하다 [우롱하다]</dt><br>
<dd>ridicule; jeer at; deride</dd><br>
<dd>남을 어리석고 하찮게 여겨 함부로 대하거나 놀리다.</dd><br>
<dd>To consider someone foolish and insignificant, and thus treat him/her disrespectfully or make fun of him/her.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>비웃다 [비ː욷따]</dt><br>
<dd>laugh mockingly; jeer at; ridicule</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 사람, 또는 그의 행동을 터무니없거나 어처구니없다고 여겨 흉을 보듯이 기분 나쁘게 웃다.</dd><br>
<dd>To laugh at someone displeasingly for doing an absurd or ridiculous act.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>갉다 [각따]</dt><br>
<dd>1. scratch; scrape; nibble</dd><br>
<dd>날카로운 것으로 조금씩 긁거나 뜯다.</dd><br>
<dd>To scratch or scrape away something with something sharp.</dd><br>
<dd>2. criticize; ridicule</dd><br>
<dd>남을 헐뜯거나 비꼬다.</dd><br>
<dd>To criticize or make sarcastic remarks about someone.</dd><br>
<dd>3. extort; steal</dd><br>
<dd>남의 재물을 나쁜 방법으로 빼앗다.</dd><br>
<dd>To take someone's property with dishonest or illegal means.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>